<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={4.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={7.25}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={7.97}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={4.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={7.25}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={7.97}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>30</li><li>64.99</li><li>85.46</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}^{{2}}={7.25}^{{2}}+{7.97}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({7.25}\right)}{\left({7.97}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{16}={52.5625}+{63.5209}-{115.565}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{100.0834}=-{115.565}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.86603556440099}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={29.998835658616}={30}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({29.998835658616}\right)}}}}{{4.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{7.25}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1.7911316321451}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left(-{1.7911316321451}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={64.987843809076}\approx{64.99}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{29.998835658616}+{64.987843809076}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={85.464801421507}\approx{85.46}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

